  "texts": [
    "Analysis of proofread data has so far relied on static exports after proofreading is completed.",
    "For instance, NeuPrint 27 provides analysis of data after it has been proofread in NeuTu.",
    "In theory, it can also use exports and materialized snapshots from CAVE.",
    "Although the reliance on static data is limiting for use during proofreading, such tools can provide more complex analyses, such as graph queries, through preprocessing of the synapse graph 51, as illustrated by NeuPrint 27 (https://neuprint.janelia.org), Codex (http://codex.flywire.ai) and FlyBrainLab 52.",
    "Connectomics data, and biological imaging data in general, are being generated at a growing rate."
  ],
